parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering assist can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering assist fault warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to steer
the power steering assist fault message appears on the instrument panel
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates
and the vehicle may lose power steering while driving.
